    {
        "content": "<p>Hi all,</p>\n<p>After upgrading to Vite 8, we're seeing the following build-time error:</p>\n<p>[ILLEGAL_REASSIGNMENT] Error: Unexpected re-assignment of const variable <code>storagePtr</code></p>\n<p>It appears in JS code generated by jco, for example:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"JavaScript\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kd\">function</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nx\">_liftFlatRecord</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nx\">keysAndLiftFns</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"k\">return</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kd\">function</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nx\">_liftFlatRecordInner</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nx\">ctx</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"nx\">_debugLog</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s1\">'[_liftFlatRecord()] args'</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nx\">ctx</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">});</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"kd\">const</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nx\">memory</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nx\">useDirectParams</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nx\">storagePtr</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nx\">storageLen</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nx\">params</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nx\">ctx</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">if</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nx\">useDirectParams</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">      </span><span class=\"nx\">storagePtr</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nx\">params</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"mf\">0</span><span class=\"p\">];</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\">// &lt;-- re-assignment causes ILLEGAL_REASSIGNMENT</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Dev mode works fine, but production build fails. Has anyone encountered this before, or have suggestions for handling const reassignment in generated code?</p>",
        "id": 579845143,
        "sender_full_name": "ktz_alias",
        "timestamp": 1773717629
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>As a workaround, changing the destructured binding from <code>const</code> to <code>let</code> avoids the error.</p>",
        "id": 579845167,
        "sender_full_name": "ktz_alias",
        "timestamp": 1773717658
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>jco 1.16.1 also generates the same code, but vite 7.3.1 does not report an error.<br>\nThe issue becomes visible when using jco 1.17.0.</p>",
        "id": 579845198,
        "sender_full_name": "ktz_alias",
        "timestamp": 1773717690
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Thanks for the report <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"1001980\">@ktz_alias</span> ! Will have a bug fix release out soon</p>",
